===Glyph origin===
{{Han etym}}
Originally written as {{och-l|*韋|to surround}}. Now {{Han compound|囗|t1=enclosure|韋|c1=s|c2=p|ls=psc|nocap=y}}.

===Etymology===
Likely borrowed from some reflex of {{cog|mkh-pro|*wil|t=to turn}}. Compare {{cog|km|វិល|t=to revolve}}, {{cog|my|ဝေ့|t=to whirl around}} ({{zh-ref|Schuessler, 2007}}).

